Reasoning: The paper discusses the Sequential Subspace Optimization (SESOP) framework and its applications in various areas such as signal/image denoising, deconvolution, compressive sensing, computed tomography, diffraction imaging, and support vector machines. These areas are typically associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of numerical analysis (cs.NA), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
